 <h2 style="background-color:lightpink;"> Documents Required for Learner License </h2>
<p>The applicant must submit the documents given below, before taking the Learner's License test for the Learner's License application to be processed by the RTO.</p>

<h3>Learner's License test appointment receipt</h3>
        <ol>
<p>Completely filled Form No. 2</p>
<p>Completely filled Form 1 (physical fitness declaration) and Form 1 A, a medical certificate to be provided by a certified medical practitioner, in case of Learner's License application for heavy & transport vehicles and for candidates aged above 50 years.
</p>
  <h3>address proof, which can be any of the following documents.</h3>
<p>Aadhaar Card</p>
<p>Voter ID</p>
<p>Recent Electricity bills or telephone bills</p>
<p>Ration Card</p>
            </ol>
<h3>Age Proof, which can be any of the following documents</h3>
        <ol>
<p>Life insurance policy, Ration Card</p>
<p>Voter ID card</p>
<p>Birth certificate</p>
<p>Passport</p>
            </ol>
<p>Recent passport size photographs of the applicant</p>
<p>If the individual is applying for a Learner's License for Transport vehicle, he must produce the 
    original driving license held by him for at least a year for Light Motor Vehicle.</p>
<h3>How to apply for a Learner's License </h3>
<p>The procedure of applying for a Learner's License in Maharashtra is very simple and applicants can
     make use of the Maharashtra Motor Vehicle Department online portal to get all information about documents
     and procedures required for Learner's License. Given below is the procedure of applying for a Learner's License .</p>
<ol>
<p>To obtain a Learner's License, the candidate must first take a test for the same. 
    The candidate can book a slot online to take the Learner's License test in Maharashtra. 
    Alternatively, the candidate can also reach out to the nearest RTO office to book a slot for Learner's License test.</p>
<p>The applicant must submit all necessary documents including KYC documents
     and application form at the RTO before taking the Learner's License test.</p>
<p>If the candidate is applying for a Transport Vehicle license, the original copy of his 
    permanent DL which was issued at least an year back must be presented at the RTO.</p>
<p>Before taking the Learner's License test, the candidate must also pay 
    a nominal fee of Rs. 30 for each class of vehicle at the RTO. The test
     will be a computer based test that will test the applicant’s knowledge of road signs and safety.</p>
<p>The applicant must be present at the test centre on given time and
     date to take the test. Upon completing the Learner's License test successfully,
     the copy of original Learner's License will be sent to the residence of applicant.</p>
 </ol>

